SYNOPSIS
	mixed get_error_file(string name, int flag)

DESCRIPTION
	Return the name of the file where a compilation error occured.
	
	If there is an error associated to the wizard given by name
	name, then an array of 4 elements is returned. They are the
	filename where the error occured, the line number where it
	occurs, the error message and the forget flag respectively. If
	no error was found, 0 is returned.

	If the flag is set, the error will be forgotten.

SEE ALSO
	ed(E), valid_read(M)
